13/07/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- During a visit to Serbia-Montenegro on Tuesday (12 July), World Bank President Paul Wolfowitz praised economic and social developments in the countries of Southeast Europe. He described the progress achieved during the previous decade as encouraging and said he hoped the Bank could provide assistance there over the next 10-15 years. Wolfowitz stopped in Belgrade after Monday's ceremony in Potocari, marking the 10th anniversary of the Srebrenica massacre. (B92, RTS, Beta, Tanjug - 12/07/05)
